{"word":"πέρθω","slug":"πέρθω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πέρθω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:syncopated'>syncop.</a> aor2 <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>πέρθαι</el>, like <el>δέχθαι</el> from <a href='S:δέχομαι'><el>δέχομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to waste, ravage, sack, destroy</i>, a town, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of persons, <i>to destroy, slay</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of love, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>of things, <i>to destroy</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to get by plunder</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}